@startuml ClaudeCodeTopology
!includeurl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/refs/heads/main/proveo.iuml
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho

left to right direction

title Claude Code Topology — ML Blackbox Algorithm

actor "Human" as Human
actor "Claude Code" as Claude

package "Harness Layer" as Harness {
 component "entrypoint.sh\n(docker)" as Entrypoint <<script>>
 component ".env loader\nmodel bridge" as EnvLoader <<logic>>
 component "smoke-test mode" as Smoke <<mode>>
 component "CLAUDE.md\n(loop spec)" as ClaudeMd <<prompt>>
}

package "Execution Loop" as Loop {
 component "Spec / Goal" as Spec <<step>>
 component "Plan + Acceptance Criteria" as Plan <<step>>
 component "Implement (edit)" as Implement <<step>>
 component "Verify (run tests/lint)" as Verify <<step>>
 component "Inspect Failure → Adjust" as Inspect <<step>>
}

package "Container Sandbox" as Sandbox {
 component "--dangerously-skip-permissions" as Perms <<flag>>
 component "tmpfs mounts\n/workspace/{input,output,temp}" as Mounts <<storage>>
 component "network egress layer\nbroker|proxy|firewall" as Net <<security>>
 component "runs as host uid\n(non-root)" as User <<security>>
}

Human --> Entrypoint : starts container
Entrypoint --> EnvLoader
Entrypoint --> Smoke
Entrypoint --> Claude : exec claude
Claude --> ClaudeMd : reads loop rules
Claude --> Loop : executes loop
Loop --> Verify : runs detected commands
Verify --> Inspect : on failure
Inspect --> Plan : next iteration
Claude --> Perms : full tool access
Perms --> Sandbox : within container boundary

note right of Loop
Loop pattern:
1. State goal + acceptance criteria
2. Identify verification commands
3. Implement smallest change
4. Run verification
5. Inspect result, repeat or stop
end note

note bottom of Sandbox
Safety boundary is the container + its network,
not tool permissions. The network egress layer
(broker|proxy|firewall) is what makes
the dangerous in-container posture acceptable —
see ""claudecode-egress-topology.puml"".
end note

Net ..> Perms : network containment offsets full tool consent

@enduml
